Roast the carrots: Preheat the #oven{} to 400 degrees. Peel then halve the 
@baby carrots{16%oz}, then cut into wedges (like steak fries). Toss the carrots 
on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @olive oil{1%tsp} and a pinch of 
@salt{} and @black pepper{}. Place in the oven for about ~{25-35%minutes}, 
until soft and caramelized.

Halve, peel, and mince the @yellow onion{1}(halved, peeled, and minced). Heat 
@butter{4%tbsp} in a medium oven-proof pan over medium heat. Add the onion 
to the pan and cook, tossing, for ~{5-6%minutes}, until very soft. Add the 
@milk{16%oz} and @water{1%cup} to the pan and bring to a boil. Add the 
@shell pasta{6%oz} to the pan and cook, stirring very often, until pasta is 
al dente and sauce has thickened, ~{10-12%minutes}.

> TIP: If the sauce becomes too thick before the pasta is al dente, simply add 
a splash of water.

A few minutes before the macaroni is ready, remove the roasted carrots from 
the oven and set the #broiler{} to high (or oven to 500 degrees). In a 
#small bowl{}, combine the @panko breadcrumbs{1/4%cup} with a drizzle of 
@olive oil{1%tsp}, and a pinch of @salt{} and @black pepper{}.

Remove the pan from heat and stir in the @cheddar cheese{4%oz}. If you do not 
have an oven-proof pan, now is the time to transfer the mixture to a 
#9x13 baking dish{}. Sprinkle with the panko mixture and place under the 
broiler for ~{2-3%minutes}, until golden brown.

Serve the macaroni and cheese straight out of the #skillet{}, with the roasted 
carrots to the side. Enjoy!